# B2Bware DataHub API — Cursor Rules

You are an expert on the B2Bware DataHub API, a modular B2B commerce platform with 9 specialized Hubs.

## Key Facts

- Base URL pattern: `https://{domain}/api/v1/apps/{hub-slug}/{resource}`
- Auth: Bearer token in `Authorization` header on all requests (except public CDN/webhook endpoints)
- Required headers: `Authorization: Bearer {token}`, `Accept: application/json`, `Content-Type: application/json` (POST/PUT/PATCH)
- All list endpoints are paginated: `?page=1&per_page=25`
- Sorting: `?sort=-_created_at,name` (prefix `-` for descending)
- Filtering uses MongoDB-compatible JSON syntax: `?filter[field]=[{"condition":"=","value":"active"}]`
- Includes use comma-separated dot notation: `?include=price,mainMedia,categories.category`

## Hub Slugs

- `product-hub` — Products, categories, pricing, stock, media, variations, vendors
- `order-hub` — Orders, carts, checkout, quotes, payments
- `customer-hub` — Customers, companies, addresses, roles, groups
- `attributes-hub` — Dynamic attributes, types, values, groups
- `media-hub` — Polymorphic media with Bunny CDN proxy
- `notification-hub` — Multi-channel notifications (120+ endpoints)
- `tax-hub` — Tax calculation, rules, jurisdictions
- `settings-hub` — Platform config, locales, currencies, cache
- `license-hub` — License key lifecycle management

## Filter Operators

`=`, `!=`, `>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`, `LIKE`, `IN`, `NOT IN`, `EMPTY`, `NOT EMPTY`

Combine with `"operator": "AND"` or `"operator": "OR"` in condition arrays.

Relation filters use dot notation: `filter[company.name]=[...]`

Callback filters use simple key=value: `filter[search]=term`

## ProductHub Special Filters

- `filter[attribute]` — JSON array: `[{"attribute_id":1,"attribute_value":"Red","condition":"IN","operator":"AND"}]`
- `filter[exclude_child_products]=1` — Hide variation children
- `filter[exclude_parent_products]=1` — Hide configurable parents
- `filter[anchor_category_id]=5` — Category + all descendants
- `filter[parent_id]=50` — Only children of product 50
- `filter[search]=term` — Full-text across name, sku, description
- `filter[without_stock]=1` — Exclude products with no stock

## Product Types

- `simple` — Standalone product
- `configurable` — Parent with child variations (product_type is immutable after creation)
- `license` — Product with license key generation
- `dt-one` — Digital product

## Checkout Flow

1. Create cart: `POST /carts` or `PATCH /carts` (upsert by session_uuid)
2. Add items: `POST /cart-items`
3. Preview: `GET /carts/{id}/checkout`
4. Complete: `POST /carts/{id}/checkout` with shipping_method_id, billing_method_id, shipping_address_id, billing_address_id

## Tax Calculation

`POST /tax-hub/calculate` with `line_items` (subtotal, tax_class_id) and `customer` (email, country, region, customer_group, vat_number)

Rate fallback: Matched rule → Class+jurisdiction mapping → Country rate → GLOBAL jurisdiction → Config default

## Bulk Operations

- `PUT /product-hub/products/bulk/update` — Bulk update products
- `PUT /product-hub/products/upsert/single` — Upsert by SKU (action: createOrUpdate/onlyCreate/onlyUpdate)
- `POST /product-hub/stock/upsert/bulk` — Bulk upsert stock
- `POST /product-hub/prices/upsert/bulk` — Bulk upsert prices
- `PUT /attributes-hub/attributes/insert/bulk` — Bulk create/update attributes
- `POST /notification-hub/notifications/create-bulk` — Bulk notifications (max 10,000)
- `POST /license-hub/license-keys/generate` — Generate keys (max 1,000)

## Coding Guidelines

1. Always use environment variables for domain and token (DATAHUB_DOMAIN, DATAHUB_TOKEN)
2. Handle pagination — iterate current_page to last_page
3. Use upsert endpoints for sync workflows to avoid duplicates
4. URL-encode filter JSON values properly
5. Only retry 5xx errors with exponential backoff; fix 4xx before retrying
6. Use includes judiciously — only request what you need
7. Prefer IN operator over chaining OR conditions
8. Use anchor_category_id for category trees (includes subcategories)
9. Use exclude_child_products=1 on product listings
10. Never expose API tokens in client-side code

## Error Handling

- 200 OK, 201 Created, 204 No Content (DELETE)
- 400 Bad Request (malformed JSON/params)
- 401 Unauthorized (missing/invalid token)
- 403 Forbidden (insufficient permissions)
- 404 Not Found
- 422 Validation Error: `{"message": "...", "errors": {"field": ["Error."]}}`
- 500 Server Error

## Product Includes (most common)

`price`, `specialPrice`, `finalPrice`, `costPrice`, `tierPrices`, `groupPrices`, `stock`, `stock.warehouse`, `mainMedia`, `media`, `categories.category`, `attributeValues.value.translation`, `childProducts.childProduct`, `variationAttributes`, `stockSum`, `attributes`, `crossSells.crossSellProduct`, `upSells.upSellProduct`, `vendorProduct.vendor`, `translation`, `licenseConfiguration`

## Order Includes (most common)

`customer`, `customer.company`, `orderLineItems`, `orderLineItems.product.mainMedia`, `shippingMethod`, `billingMethod`, `shippingAddress`, `billingAddress`, `comments`

## Customer Includes (most common)

`company`, `role`, `shippingAddresses`, `billingAddresses`, `customerGroup`, `attributeValues.value.translation`

## Notification Channels

`email`, `database`, `broadcast`, `sms`, `push`, `slack`

## License Key Statuses

`available`, `assigned`, `activated`, `expired`, `revoked`

